 employment and internships posted by employers To access the site  type in your UIC EMAIL address  including  uic edu  as your username  then hit FORGOT PASSWORD  In a few minutes mail address  Follow the link to set up your password and log in  If you do not receive the welcome message with an hour  please call the Career Services office at              for assistance              In order to apply to jobs  you need to fill out the required information on your profile and upload your resume  nAre UIC graduates  alumni  allowed to use your services  nYou may use the services of the Career Services office for one year after you graduate  After that  you may refer to our Alumni page for additional options Alumni  nIf I graduated over a year ago  may I still use UICcareers com  nAfter one year  please contact the Career Services office to regain access to UICcareers com Career Services office  UICcareers com  nAre graduates of UIUC and UIS allowed to use your services  nUnfortunately  our services are limited to UIC students  nHow do I get help with interviewing  nYou may get help through the Interviews and Networking page on our website  scheduling an advising appointment for advice  or requesting a one on Note  There is a limit of one mock interview session per student per semester Interviews  Networking  advising appointment  nHow do I get help with my resume and or cover letter  nWe offer drop in career advising for resumes and cover letters a few times a week  Check the website for walk  You may also schedule an advising appointment  attend a workshop  or review our Resume   Cover Letter section on the website hours advising appointment workshop Resume   Cover Letter   nHow do I get help with choosing a major and or thinking about careers  nYou may start the conversation during drop in hours  However  an in depth  one on one career advising session is recommended  You can also review the Career Exploration section on the website for additional ideas and tools to assist you one on one career advising session Career Exploration  nWhen can I schedule a mock interview  nYou may schedule a mock interview on weekdays between      am and     pm  including over breaks  by calling the Career Services office at                            nHow do I schedule an advising appointment  nYou may schedule an appointment by calling the Career Services office at                            nIf I missed my advising appointment  may I reschedule  nYou may reschedule your appointment up to three times  After that you may no longer make appointments  you may only use walk in advising  nMay I make an appointment for the same day I call  nWhile we do not offer same day appointments  you may come in during walk in advising hours for assistance walk in advising hours  nDo I have to meet with the advisor that specializes in my major  Can I meet with a different advisor each time I come in  nYou may choose to meet with a different advisor if you like  but we recommend you first speak with the advisor that specializes in your field if your schedule allows Is your office the only career services office  nDepending on your field of study  you may also seek service from other career centers on campus other career centers on campus About About  n nBack to main content n n n n n n Back to main content Hours   Location Our Services Contact Us Social Media Staff Directory Career Peer Mentors Other Career Centers Frequently Asked Questions  n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n          Career Services n         Students Career Planning Guide Make an Appointment FAQs Employers Post a Position Employer Partner Program UICcareers com Campus Partners Campus Partners Program Workshop Request Forms Footer Menu Career Programs and Events UICcareers UIC Student Employment Office Contact                             careerservices uic edu Social Media Accounts  nFacebook n Facebook  nTwitter n Twitter  nYouTube n YouTube UIC edu links UIC edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus